<plot>A personal and thought-provoking look into the story of CFB Gagetown, a sprawling military base in New Brunswick, Canada, that was sprayed with more chemical herbicides per acre than Vietnam. These chemicals have caused sickness and death in hundreds of thousands of people, but the Canadian government has systematically denied any responsibility for its actions and shamefully abandoned her veterans. This film will tell the David and Goliath story of their fight for justice and acceptance in the face of bureaucratic lies, deception, and denials.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?208508</url></doc>
